summary:
I am a Service, Quality and InfoSec Management consultant who works from a human perspective, advising and supporting companies who want to streamline their Service Management processes and organisation. The goal is to provide services in a more efficient and cost-effective way, leading to higher customer satisfaction and improved business results.

I do this based on a unique combination of skills and experience:
- 25 years experience in the ICT industry;
- 15 years people and business management experience;
- Lead Auditor ISO 9001, ISO/IEC 20000-1, ISO 22301 and ISO/IEC 27001;
- ITIL 4 Managing Professional and Strategic Leader;
- Author of various books on Service Management, Governance incl. ISO/IEC 20000-1 and ISO/IEC 38500;
- Information Security certifications: ISO/IEC 27001 Lead Auditor, CISSP, CISM, CRISC;
- Author of several books on Service Management, Governance, and Psychotherapy;
- Certified coach and psychotherapist.
